==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*umbi'', from Indo-European ''*ambhi'' ‘around’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[umbi]] (Dutch [[om]]), Old High German [[umbi]] (German [[um]]), Old Norse [[umb]] (Swedish [[om]]).  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[ambi-]], Greek [[αμφι]], Old Irish [[imb-]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ymb/

===Preposition===
'''ymb'''
# [[around]], [[about]], [[by]], [[concerning]]

